The paper deals with measuring the nonlinearity of pseudorandom sequences, which is a common topic in the field of cryptography (cs.CR). The proposed model is based on neural networks (cs.NE) and involves predicting the strength of binary sequences, which can be seen as a problem in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves some computational aspects, such as calculating the Unique Window Size, which could be relevant to the sub-category of computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the use of neural networks for prediction is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
